				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, it's kind of crazy: it's using the DMC to count the number of cycles the sequence of code takes, while at the same time having DMC DMA occur at a particular point in the code.
<br />
<br />The _512 variant just has the DMC DMA occur 512 clocks later in the test code, so you add $200 to the time column to see the real offset. The only difference in the ROM would be a couple of delay values, and the CRC.
<br />
<br /><strong>EDIT:</strong> <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Emulator_tests#APU" class="postlink">newer APU tests</a> on the wiki.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

